        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh hardens provider setup flow projection: manifest auth choices and install-catalog setup rows are copied through bounded readers before contribution construction, so one unreadable setup row does not hide healthy setup choices\n- also preserved the rebased provider hook-ref guard on current `main`; unreadable provider id/alias/hook-alias rows no longer abort runtime hook lookup for healthy providers\n- keeps the draft PR branch updated as work continues; current head is `a4c8713f8886e9a1997c3de8c5cd87fe325b5147`, proven on `origin/main` at `095bc6d4b4105ca89a71a82d20f8de5b7df9fe9b`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/provider-runtime.test.ts --reporter=verbose -t \"skips unreadable provider hook refs\"`: 1 file passed, 1 test passed / 55 skipped\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/flows/provider-flow.test.ts --reporter=verbose`: 1 file passed, 11 tests passed\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/flows/provider-flow.ts src/flows/provider-flow.test.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-hook-runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/flows/provider-flow.ts src/flows/provider-flow.test.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-hook-runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode commit --commit 2e14800302a --base 2e14800302a^`: clean before final rebase; same provider setup patch replayed cleanly\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode commit --commit cf24325edc0 --base cf24325edc0^`: clean before final rebase; same provider hook-ref patch replayed cleanly\n- `OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run -provider blacksmith-testbox -shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`: blocked before remote execution because Blacksmith is not authenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required)\n- scrubbed touched files/spec/PR body for the reported plugin name and private local paths\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, provider/runtime/channel/plugin registry projections, model/provider install catalog projections, web search install catalog projection, model picker provider catalog projection, web search setup provider projection, provider model-picker flow projection, provider setup flow projection, and provider runtime hook-ref projection no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable env vars, unreadable install/provider metadata, unreadable catalog hooks, unreadable setup provider rows, unreadable setup choices, or unreadable model-picker contribution rows while healthy sibling registrations continue where the surface is availability-oriented and security-sensitive policy/scope failures fail closed.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, based on `origin/main` at `095bc6d4b4105ca89a71a82d20f8de5b7df9fe9b`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: after the provider setup flow slice and final rebase, ran focused Vitest for the provider hook-ref conflict surface and provider setup/model-picker flow surface, formatting, linting, commit diff check, synthetic/private-name scrub, autoreview on the current-slice and conflict-slice commits before final clean replay, and attempted the Blacksmith-backed changed gate listed in Verification.\n\nEvidence after fix: `provider-flow.test.ts` seeds unreadable `fuzzplugin` manifest auth choices and unreadable `fuzzplugin` install-catalog setup rows while proving healthy `mockplugin` setup choices remain visible. `provider-runtime.test.ts` covers unreadable provider hook refs while proving healthy provider hook lookup remains available.\n\nObserved result after fix: malformed setup-flow metadata no longer aborts provider setup contribution construction before healthy rows are reached; malformed provider hook-ref metadata no longer aborts runtime hook lookup before healthy providers are reached.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate did not run because the local Blacksmith CLI is unauthenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required). AWS Crabbox broad gate was not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted provider-flow/provider-runtime surfaces plus formatter/lint/autoreview checks.\n",
